WHO   — The Whipped-Cream Scene — the poster · the era's gaze
WHAT  — The era's gaze: the objectifying late-'90s teen-movie spectacle that made the poster and dates the hardest now.
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's surface is genuinely raunchy '90s, and honesty means naming how it shoots its young women.
